<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="662" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="62.[173,1379,301,886]" pageId="62" pageNumber="662">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,285,420,454]" pageId="62" pageNumber="662">Habitat.</emphasis>
Few records, from a range of natural and anthropogenic habitats including lowland forest, bamboo thickets, coconut groves, and a residential area close to secondary forest. One specimen was trapped in rafters of a building in a beach-front coconut grove. It thus appears moderately tolerant of habitat disturbance. Mostly near sea level, but one record at 250 m on Palawan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="662" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="62.[173,1379,301,886]" pageId="62" pageNumber="662">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,436,617,651]" pageId="62" pageNumber="662">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The Palawan Pencil-tailed Tree Mouseis likely to be primarily herbivorous..
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
